<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The car of a woman who disappeared ten days ago has been found abandoned in a gorge.</p>

<p>Rebekah Storey, 29, was reported missing from Tauranga, in the Bay of Plenty, on New Zealand's North Island, on September 9.</p>

<p>Her car was found abandoned in Waioeka gorge, between Opotiki and Gisborne, on Wednesday.</p>

<p>Rebekah Storey, 29, was reported missing from Tauranga, in the Bay of Plenty, on New Zealand's North Island, on September 9 </p>

<p>The Suzuki Swift has a licence plate of CWD620.</p>

<p>Police are urging anyone who may have seen Ms Storey or her vehicle to come forward. </p>

<p>Her family are seriously worried about Ms Storey's wellbeing.</p>

<p>Anyone with information is asked to contact New Zealand Police on 105 with the number 200909/2598.</p>

